<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Score Rise Kit - Professional Dispute Templates</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
        @media print {
            .no-print { display: none; }
            .page-break { page-break-after: always; }
            body { background: white; }
            .letter-container { border: none; box-shadow: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-100 font-serif text-gray-900 leading-relaxed">

    <!-- Navigation / Header -->
    <div class="no-print bg-white border-b sticky top-0 z-10 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex justify-between items-center">
            <h1 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800">Score Rise Kit Templates</h1>
            <button onclick="window.print()" class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition font-sans">
                Print Letters
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 md:p-8 space-y-12">

        <!-- LETTER 1: PERSONAL INFORMATION SWEEP -->
        <section class="letter-container bg-white p-8 md:p-12 shadow-md rounded-sm page-break border border-gray-200">
            <div class="text-right text-sm mb-8 font-sans">
                <p>[Current Date]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">(Your Name)</p>
                <p>[Your Current Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
                <p>DOB: [Date of Birth]</p>
                <p>SSN: [Social Security Number]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">[Credit Bureau Name]</p>
                <p>[Bureau Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6">
                <p class="font-bold underline text-center">RE: FORMAL DISPUTE OF INACCURATE PERSONAL INFORMATION</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <p>To Whom It May Concern,</p>
                <p>I am writing to formally dispute several items in the personal information section of my credit report. Maintaining an accurate credit profile is my right under the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA).</p>
                <p>The following information is inaccurate, outdated, or belongs to another individual and must be deleted immediately:</p>
                
                <ul class="list-disc ml-8 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Incorrect Names/Aliases:</strong> [List any misspelled names or names that aren't yours]</li>
                    <li><strong>Old/Incorrect Addresses:</strong> [List specific old addresses you want removed]</li>
                    <li><strong>Incorrect Employers:</strong> [List incorrect or old employment entries]</li>
                </ul>

                <p>These inaccuracies can lead to mixed files and identity confusion. Please update my file to reflect only my current, correct information as provided in the attached documentation. Please send me an updated copy of my credit report once these deletions have been completed.</p>
                
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <div class="mt-8">
                    <p class="border-t border-gray-400 w-64 pt-2">[Signature]</p>
                    <p>(Your Name)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- LETTER 2: ROUND 1 FACTUAL DISPUTE -->
        <section class="letter-container bg-white p-8 md:p-12 shadow-md rounded-sm page-break border border-gray-200">
            <div class="text-right text-sm mb-8 font-sans">
                <p>[Current Date]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">(Your Name)</p>
                <p>[Your Current Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
                <p>SSN: [Social Security Number]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">[Credit Bureau Name]</p>
                <p>[Bureau Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6 text-center">
                <p class="font-bold underline italic">CERTIFIED MAIL - RETURN RECEIPT REQUESTED</p>
                <p class="font-bold underline mt-2">NOTICE OF DISPUTE: REQUEST FOR INVESTIGATION UNDER FCRA SECTION 611</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <p>To the Dispute Department,</p>
                <p>I am reviewing my credit report and noticed several items that are being reported inaccurately. Under the Fair Credit Reporting Act, 15 U.S.C. § 1681i, I am exercising my right to dispute these items.</p>
                
                <p>Please investigate and provide verification for the following accounts:</p>
                
                <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 mt-4 mb-4">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                            <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left">Account Name</th>
                            <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left">Account Number</th>
                            <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left">Reason for Dispute</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">[Creditor Name]</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">[Account #]</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">This account is inaccurate. I am requesting full physical verification of this debt.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">[Creditor Name]</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">[Account #]</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">The balance and payment history reported are incorrect. Please delete if unverified.</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <p>If you are unable to verify these items within the 30-day period allowed by law, you must remove them immediately. If this investigation does not resolve my dispute, please provide the name and address of the person you contacted for verification.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.</p>
                
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <div class="mt-8">
                    <p class="border-t border-gray-400 w-64 pt-2">[Signature]</p>
                    <p>(Your Name)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- LETTER 3: METHOD OF VERIFICATION (MOV) -->
        <section class="letter-container bg-white p-8 md:p-12 shadow-md rounded-sm border border-gray-200">
            <div class="text-right text-sm mb-8 font-sans">
                <p>[Current Date]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">(Your Name)</p>
                <p>[Your Current Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
                <p>SSN: [Social Security Number]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-8">
                <p class="font-bold">[Credit Bureau Name]</p>
                <p>[Bureau Address]</p>
                <p>[City, State, Zip Code]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6">
                <p class="font-bold underline text-center">FORMAL REQUEST FOR DESCRIPTION OF REINVESTIGATION PROCEDURE (MOV)</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <p>To Whom It May Concern,</p>
                <p>I recently received the results of my dispute regarding the accounts listed below. You stated that these items were "verified." However, I have reason to believe that a proper investigation was not conducted.</p>
                
                <p>Pursuant to 15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(7), I am formally requesting a <strong>Description of the Procedure</strong> used to verify the following information:</p>
                
                <ul class="list-disc ml-8 space-y-2">
                    <li>[Account Name / Account Number]</li>
                    <li>[Account Name / Account Number]</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Please provide the following within 15 days:</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal ml-8 space-y-1">
                    <li>The name, business address, and telephone number of any individual or business contacted during the reinvestigation.</li>
                    <li>A copy of the documentation used to verify the accuracy of the disputed information.</li>
                    <li>An explanation of the method used to verify that this account belongs to me.</li>
                </ol>

                <p>Generic "verified" responses through e-OSCAR are not sufficient evidence of a meaningful reinvestigation. Failure to provide this information is a violation of the FCRA.</p>
                
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <div class="mt-8">
                    <p class="border-t border-gray-400 w-64 pt-2">[Signature]</p>
                    <p>(Your Name)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>

    <div class="no-print text-center text-gray-500 text-sm py-8">
        End of Score Rise Kit Templates. Designed for professional credit dispute workflows.
    </div>

</body>
</html>
